6 An Act relating to health insurance; defining terms;
requiring coverage of certain anesthesia services;
7 providing for codification; and providing an
effective date.
8
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
11 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
12 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 7500 of Title 36, unless there
13 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
14 A. As used in this section:
15 1. “Anesthesia time” means the period beginning when an
16 anesthesia practitioner begins to prepare the patient for anesthesia
17 services in the operating room or an equivalent area and ends when
18 the anesthesia practitioner is no longer furnishing anesthesia
19 services to the patient. In counting anesthesia time for services
20 furnished, the anesthesia practitioner may include blocks of time
21 around an interruption in anesthesia time provided the anesthesia
22 practitioner is furnishing continuous anesthesia care within the
23 time periods around the interruption;
24
