1 2. “Payments for anesthesia service” means the prevailing
2 medical coding and billing standards in the professional medical
3 billing community including, but not limited to, current AMA CPT
4 Codebook, Medicare Claims Processing Manual, and American Society of
5 Anesthesiologists guidance. Payment for anesthesia services is
6 based on base plus time unit together multiplied by an anesthesia
7 conversion factor. Anesthesia time units are recognized in
8 appropriate time intervals that must add up to the duration of the
9 anesthesia time; and
10 3. “Insurer” shall have the same meaning as defined in Section
11 1250.2 of Title 36 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
12 B. No insurer shall establish, implement, or enforce any
13 policy, practice, or procedure which:
14 1. Imposes a time limit on the amount of covered anesthesia
15 services provided during a medical or surgical procedure; or
16 2. Restricts or excludes coverage or payment of anesthesia
17 time.
18 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
